  "prompt": "Can I get arrested for downloading movies from torent in India?",
  "response": "In India, downloading movies from torrent sites can lead to legal consequences. The country has strict copyright laws, and the Cinematograph Act of 1952 and the Copyright Act of 1957 govern the distribution and viewing of copyrighted content. Engaging in piracy by downloading or sharing copyrighted material without permission is illegal and can result in fines or imprisonment.\n\nThe government and copyright holders have been taking measures to curb piracy, including blocking access to torrent websites and pursuing legal action against those who distribute or download pirated content. While enforcement can vary, it's important to be aware that you could face penalties if caught.\n\nTo stay on the safe side, it's advisable to use legal streaming services or purchase movies from authorized sources. If you have any further questions or need more detailed legal advice, consider consulting with a legal professional.",
